# Google Sheets API Configuration
# Get these values from Google Cloud Console and Google Sheets

# Google Sheets API Key (Public API Key with restrictions)
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_KEY=your_google_sheets_api_key_here

# Google Sheets ID (From the URL of your Google Sheet)
# Example: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1BxiMVs0XRA5nFMdKvBdBZjgmUUqptlbs74OgvE2upms/edit
# The ID is: 1BxiMVs0XRA5nFMdKvBdBZjgmUUqptlbs74OgvE2upms
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_SHEETS_ID=your_google_sheets_id_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a Google Sheet with columns: Timestamp, Name, Email, Subject, Message, Consent
# 2. Share the sheet as "Anyone with the link can view" (for public API access)
# 3. Go to Google Cloud Console, create a project, and enable Google Sheets API
# 4. Create an API key with domain restrictions (your website domain)
# 5. Copy the API key and Sheet ID to these environment variables
# 6. Rename this file to .env.local and add your actual values
